tags.name: Santo Domingo Pueblo / Kewa
tags.note: While the display names of the Pueblo have changed to "Kewa Pueblo", the Tribe's official name remains "Santo Domingo Pueblo"

tags.description: The original name of this small valley within the East Fork of the Jemez River watershed, was called "Vallecitos de los Indios". That place name is visible as early as the 1880s on USGS maps.
tags.name: Sierra de los Pinos
tags.note: "Sierra de los Pinos" was a name given to this housing subdivision within Sandoval County sometime after 1960.
